  },
  {
    icon: '📐',
    title: 'Qualifies Solar Scope Online',
    text: "Through conversation, the AI determines whether the visitor needs a domestic PV system, a battery retrofit, a commercial rooftop installation, or an EV charger integration. You receive a correctly categorised solar lead with roof details and consumption context."
  },
  {
    icon: '🕐',
    title: 'Converts Evening Energy Bill Frustration',
    text: "Electricity bills arrive by email at 7pm. Homeowners immediately search for solar solutions. Chat captures the enquiry at the exact moment of bill shock — when the motivation to invest in solar is strongest."
  },
  {
    icon: '📊',
    title: 'Explains Solar Options to Visitors',
    text: "Visitors ask 'how many panels do I need?', 'which battery is best?', 'what is the SEG?' The AI responds from your configured expertise — comparing GivEnergy versus Tesla, explaining MCS certification, and discussing payback — while capturing the property details."
  },
  {
    icon: '🔗',
    title: 'Works Alongside Installation Gallery',
    text: "Your website shows completed rooftop arrays, neat inverter installations, and generation monitoring dashboards. Chat converts visitors who admire your panel layouts into booked surveys."
  },
  {
    icon: '✅',
    title: 'Included at No Extra Cost',
    text: `Website chat is bundled with phone answering at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month. Unlimited solar conversations — from domestic battery queries to 200kWp commercial system tenders.`
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How do I install chat on my solar website?",
    answer: "Setup provides a JavaScript snippet for your website header — WordPress, Wix, Squarespace, or custom HTML. The branded widget appears on every page immediately. Solar firms with rooftop installation galleries, generation monitoring screenshots, and MCS certification badges displayed prominently experience strong chat engagement from visitors who have already evaluated your renewable energy credentials and want to discuss their specific roof and consumption."
  },
  {
    question: "Can the AI explain battery options to visitors?",
    answer: "Your MCS-certified company profile trains the AI with your battery expertise. When a visitor types 'should I get GivEnergy or Tesla Powerwall?' the AI explains the key differences — GivEnergy's modular expandability versus Tesla's integrated aesthetic, AC-coupled versus DC-coupled compatibility, and capacity options — while capturing the visitor's existing system details, consumption patterns, and contact information for your detailed consultation."
  },
  {
    question: "What does chat capture from solar visitors?",
    answer: "The AI records the solar requirement (new PV system, battery addition, inverter replacement, or commercial installation), the property type and roof orientation, the tile or slate material, visible shading concerns, current electricity consumption if known, battery preference, EV ownership, and the visitor's contact details for your survey follow-up."
  },
  {
    question: "Does chat slow my solar website?",
    answer: "Rooftop installation photography, generation monitoring dashboard screenshots, MCS accreditation badges, and customer review feeds load at their normal speed before the chat component activates. The lightweight widget initialises asynchronously after all visual content renders. No measurable impact on page speed or search engine positioning."
  },
  {
    question: "Is website chat a separate charge?",
    answer: `Chat arrives as part of the phone answering package at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month — zero additional cost. Solar installers gain complementary coverage: weekday phone calls from commercial property managers commissioning rooftop systems and developers requesting new-build packages, balanced with evening and weekend chats from homeowners whose electricity bills triggered immediate solar research.`
  },
  {
    question: "How is visitor data from solar queries handled?",
    answer: "Chat conversations containing property addresses, roof dimensions, energy consumption data, inverter specifications, battery preferences, and visitor contact details are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Leads go exclusively to you. No solar project details reach competitors or third-party lead aggregators."
  }
