<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI Website Chat for Solar Panel Installers | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI website chat for UK solar panel installers. Engages homeowners researching PV systems and battery storage during evening bill-shock moments. Included at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/solar-panel-installers/ai-website-chat/"
  channelName="AI Website Chat"
  tradeName="Solar Panel Installer"
  tradeNamePlural="Solar Panel Installers"
  tradeSlug="solar-panel-installers"
  headline="AI Website Chat for Solar Panel Installer Companies"
  accentWord="Solar"
  subhead="A homeowner finds your website at 9:45pm on a Thursday in March. His quarterly electricity bill arrived today — £847, up from £520 the same quarter last year. The house is a 2005 four-bedroom detached in Carterton — south-facing interlocking concrete tile roof, no shading, double garage to the east. He has spent three hours reading about solar panels, hybrid inverters, and battery storage. He types: 'Evening — I received my electricity bill today and it is out of control. Four-bed detached in Carterton, built 2005. South-facing roof, concrete tiles, no shading, approximately 40 square metres of south-facing area plus the garage roof facing east. I would like a full solar and battery system — I have been looking at Longi Hi-Mo 6 panels or JA Solar, a GivEnergy hybrid inverter with battery storage (thinking 9.5kWh to start, expandable later), and I want to connect an EV charger so the car charges from excess solar during the day. We have an electric Kia e-Niro. I need MCS certification for the Smart Export Guarantee — I have already signed up to Octopus Flux. We also want the EPC improved from D to at least C for future house value. Can you do a survey this week? What is a typical payback for this kind of system?' Without chat, he bookmarks and calls on Saturday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your MCS certification, asks about his annual electricity consumption and whether the consumer unit has spare MCB ways, and captures: Carterton 2005 4-bed detached, south concrete tile 40m² + east garage, Longi/JA Solar, GivEnergy hybrid 9.5kWh expandable, EV charger Kia e-Niro solar excess, MCS SEG Octopus Flux, EPC D-to-C, survey this week, payback question, bill £847."
  scenario="It is 1:30am on a Saturday. A commercial property developer types: 'Hello — we are completing a new build logistics warehouse in Bicester, 8,000 square metres, flat membrane roof with standing seam sections. The tenant has asked us to install solar PV as part of the lease agreement — they want to buy the generated electricity at a discounted rate through a Power Purchase Agreement. We are thinking 400kWp on the flat sections using east-west ballasted mounting, Huawei SUN2000-100KTL three-phase string inverters, and G99 application to SSEN. The structural engineer has confirmed the roof can take the additional loading. We need an MCS-certified installer who can handle this scale and provide the generation modelling for the PPA financial model. Can you handle 400kWp? What is your lead time from survey to energisation?' Without chat, he emails Monday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your commercial capability, asks about the existing three-phase supply capacity and the DNO substation location, and captures: Bicester logistics warehouse 8,000m², flat membrane + standing seam, 400kWp east-west ballasted, Huawei SUN2000-100KTL three-phase, G99 SSEN, PPA tenant, structural confirmed, MCS, generation modelling, lead time question."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-website-chat/"
  tradePageUrl="/solar-panel-installers/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Win the Carterton GivEnergy System While the £847 Bill Stings at 9:45pm"
  ctaSubhead={`A homeowner with bill shock, a south-facing roof, and a Kia e-Niro charging from solar excess needs an MCS-certified survey this week. Chat captures the Longi panels, the Octopus Flux tariff, and the EPC improvement. Included at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month.`}
